# Continue To Ship Handoff

When a work session is using `/continue`, do not keep looping with small local-only follow-ups once the current dirty set is already a coherent, intended batch.

Treat the work as ready to hand off to `/ship` when:
- the dirty files belong to one workstream
- relevant local verification has passed, or the only remaining unknown is an external CI/remote rerun
- there is no clearly higher-value local implementation step left than committing and pushing

When that state is reached:
- stop proposing another `/continue` increment
- transition into the repo's `/ship` workflow in the same turn
- stage and ship only the intended files if unrelated dirty files exist

Do not auto-handoff to `/ship` if:
- local checks are still failing
- git identity or another required pre-push precondition is missing
- there is still a meaningful local code/docs change left to make
